gomodel:SYNGO_121  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Using immunofluorescence and immuno electron microscopy it is shown that Bassoon is present at the presynaptic active zone. As controls for the immuno electron microscopy, stainings without primary antibody were performed. Hallerman et.al. 2014 provides an knockout control for the antibody. This antibody (sap7f) is a widely used marker for the active zone.. Experimental description: 30-d-old male rats were used for immunohistochemical studies. Tissue preparation for electron microscopic analysis was done as described by Richter et al. (1996)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2017-09-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_121" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

